\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

with A, E, y held constant, the amount of commodity produced and consumed
 by household is assumed to be proportional to the amount of firm's output
 used by that household.
 If the advertising reaching any household were independent of its behavior,
 then
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
